After a day at the Aquarium my family and I, including our picky 9 year old, ate here.  We really liked the food.  Nothing fancy but flavorful and filling.  Price is high but that's because of location.  We ate outside so had a great view of the harbor.  About $10-15 per order per person.  But portions were sizable and to split for two for some people or a quick bite.  Felt like a chain experience, and it may be but I am not sure.  If you want a decent bento bowl, basic sushi, etc., its not bad.

It is similar in taste to that of a in-mall hibachi restaurant, but it does poke which is gaining popularity in the east coast recently. Based on my compatriots scoring, the Poke Burrito was a 7 out of 10. It didn't have the same punch and flavor as her favorite spot, but it was still fresh and doesn't tire itself after a while. However, she was disappointed that the tuna happened to be a mash instead of whole slices, but it isn't unheard of not does it take away the taste. I chose to try the Beef Bento Box which comes with 4 California Rolls, two Beef Gyoza, a handful of Steamed Mixed Vegetables, and Rice topped with Seasoned Beef. The beef is tender and has a sweet buttery taste that coats the tongue. The rice itself is on the softer side with a small bite within the center. The gyoza is perfectly crispy without irritating the throat with a layer of oil. The California Roll could have been a bit tighter as to not break apart, but the ingredients are fresh. The steamed vegetables are good, not frozen and does not have a tap water taste that turns vegetables bitter. Overall a good meal, I would not mind eating it again. 4 stars.
